Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
Well, let us take the example for crossing thr street.  First, tell the child to think of the safety as the first thing. Before the child cross the street, he or she must take a look at the left and then the right. If there is no car at each side, then he or she can cross the street when there is no singal light.